qas.question: What boulevard turns into E.K Gaylord Boulevard?

context: Oklahoma City also has several major national and state highways within its city limits. <a0_0>Shields Boulevard<a0_0/> (US-77) continues from E.K. Gaylord Boulevard in downtown Oklahoma City and runs south eventually connecting to I-35 near the suburb of Moore. Northwest Expressway (Oklahoma State Highway 3) runs from North Classen Boulevard in north-central Oklahoma City to the northwestern suburbs.
